to install dependencies>>pip install -r requirements.txt

*>>Method 1: Install Streamlit (Recommended - Quick Fix)
Open PowerShell in your project directory and run:

powershell
# Check if pip is working
python --version
pip --version

# Install Streamlit
pip install streamlit

# Verify installation
python -m streamlit --version
If the regular streamlit command doesn't work, use this instead:

powershell
python -m streamlit run app.py
This bypasses the PATH issue by running Streamlit as a Python module.




to run >> python -m streamlit run app.py

